Get rid of undefined behavior in tListItem

See merge request armagetronad/armagetronad!159

Assume our offset to anchor is zero

offsetof is not available on our oldest platforms, so we can't use
it; plus, the offset is guaranteed to be zero in the current layout.

Replace transfer loop with simple list swaps

The loop was not only problematic (see previous commit), but also
a bit wasteful, given that linked lists can be hurled around the place
at zero cost.

Get rid of undefined behavior in tListItem

The issue was that to save compilation time and binary size,
the bulk of the linked list implementation was in a
non-templated base class and implemented in the cpp file, using
basic pointer types.
reinterpret_casts were used to convert the final list element
types to the base type and back. Which was fine, mostly... except
for the anchor pointers. These were pointers to pointers of elements,
and while the reinterpret casts between them worked, it nevertheless
was undefined behavior; we changed the value of one pointer by
accessing them as a different pointer type, which the compiler
is allowed to assume never happens.
Thus, on fedora, the compiler optimized away a loop exit condition,
causing an infinite loop when entering the server browser.

Fixes https://gitlab.com/armagetronad/armagetronad/-/issues/145
